## New Project: pixo
- **Replaces:** nfnt/resize (3,319 importers, archived Sept 2022, explicitly abandoned Feb 2018) AND disintegration/imaging (2,899 importers, 5.7k stars, dormant since March 2023, 31 open issues)
- **Why:** Both packages are the most-used pure Go image processing libraries. nfnt/resize has no go.mod, no tagged version, maintainer said "I won't look at PRs and issues anymore." disintegration/imaging hasn't been updated in 3+ years with bugs piling up. No maintained pure Go drop-in replacement exists. bimg/govips require CGo. bild (v0.14.0, July 2024) has different API, not a drop-in. x/image/draw is too low-level.
- **Package:** github.com/agentine/pixo (verified available)
- **Features:** Resize (7 interpolation filters), transform (rotate/flip), crop (anchor-based), color adjustments, blur/sharpen/effects, compositing, I/O with format detection, WebP decode, EXIF auto-orientation, functional options API
- **Compat packages:** pixo/compat/resize (drop-in for nfnt/resize) and pixo/compat/imaging (drop-in for disintegration/imaging)
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #735 (scaffolding), #736 (core resize + transform), #737 (adjust + effects + compose), #738 (I/O + compat packages), #739 (tests + benchmarks + docs)

